11 An Act relating to the Office of Juvenile Affairs;
making an appropriation; stating purpose; providing
12 an effective date; and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Office of
17 Juvenile Affairs, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from
18 the Statewide Recovery Fund (497) of the State Treasury, the sum of
19 Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000.00) or so much thereof as may be
20 necessary to address gaps in the youth services program. Such funds
21 shall be utilized in a manner consistent with the recommendations
22 adopted by the Joint Committee on Pandemic Relief Funding on April
23 15, 2026.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
Req. No. 3952 Page 1

1 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
2 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
3 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
4 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
